FT  13 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Select Appointments at Pounds 2,000 midway
Select Appointments (Holdings), the USM-quoted recruitment agency, reported
pre-tax profits of Pounds 2,000 for the six months to end-June, against
losses of Pounds 692,000. However, a tax charge of Pounds 135,000 this time
left losses per share of 0.06p, against 0.32p.
Strong growth in all markets helped turnover rise from Pounds 12.7m to
Pounds 28.8m including Pounds 485,000 from acquisitions. Since the period
end two further acquisitions have been made and more are being sought.
